@node us-csar1 "Heiko Rath, comp.sys.amiga.reviews"
@smartwrap
@{lindent 1}@{pari -1}»There are many useful bits and pieces about the OS that you'd
have a hard time finding anywhere else. [...] It comes with a
31-page index, so it's very easy to find a particular subject.
Obviously, the TeX typesetting system was used in preparing the
book and it really shows. There's just one description of the
quality: excellent. [...] It is more fun than the Amiga ROM Kernel
and Hardware Reference manuals and has a better form factor.«@{pard}@{par}

@{lindent 4}@{pari -4}--- Heiko Rath, @{" comp.sys.amiga.reviews " link ftp-csar1}, 3 December 1993@{par}
@endnode

